output.analysis:
Let me analyze this post according to our criteria:
1. Has CMF: No CMF number is present, but this doesn't automatically disqualify it as propaganda.
2. Refers to candidate: Yes, explicitly mentions "SIMION" and "George Simion" who is candidate #2 on the presidential ballot.
3. Addresses wide population: Yes, this is a paid Facebook advertisement with an estimated reach of over 1 million people and actual impressions between 5,000-6,000.
4. Electoral objective: Yes, the post explicitly calls for voting ("Votează #SIMION") and promotes a political program.
5. Journalism: No, this is clearly not journalistic content but rather a direct call to action for voting.
6. Personal opinion: No, this is a paid advertisement with clear electoral messaging.
The post contains several red flags: - Direct call to vote for a specific presidential candidate - Promoted (paid) content - Wide reach - Clear electoral message - Continues to run after campaign period ended

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: This is clearly electoral propaganda because: - Directly names a presidential candidate (George Simion) - Contains an explicit call to vote ("Votează #SIMION") - Is a paid advertisement reaching a large audience - Promotes political program points - Has clear electoral intent
conclusion.message-for-police: RedNews, pentru incalcarea articolului 55 t) din Legea 370/2004, prin publicarea si promovarea unui mesaj de propaganda electorala dupa incheierea perioadei de campanie, respectiv dupa ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024. Postarea cu ID-ul 1251511855972536 contine un indemn direct la vot pentru candidatul George Simion ("Votează #SIMION"), promoveaza programul electoral AUR si este distribuit ca reclama platita pe Facebook, cu un impact estimat intre 5000-6000 de afisari. Mesajul are un clar caracter de propaganda electorala, fiind conceput si distribuit cu scopul de a influenta optiunea de vot a alegatorilor pentru candidatul AUR la alegerile prezidentiale.
